# Trivy CVE exceptions for orkyo-foundation
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # Impact | Reason | Added: YYYY-MM-DD | Review: YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Policy: time-bound only. Review date must be within 14 days of added date.
# Remove entries once the upstream fix is available.
#
# Reviewed 2026-05-21: upgraded to KC 26.6.2 — removed netty 4.1.132 CVEs
# (CVE-2026-33870/33871 resolved) and CVE-2026-22016 (JDK 21.0.11 resolved).
# Reviewed 2026-06-09: renewed expired entries; added netty 4.1.132 → 4.1.135 CVEs
# (CVE-2026-44893/44249/45416/45674/47691) newly appearing in Trivy Java DB.
# Reviewed 2026-06-14: added CVE-2026-48059 (netty-codec-haproxy PROXY v2 DoS, also
# fixed in 4.1.135) — newly appearing in Trivy Java DB; same KC-ships-4.1.132 situation.
# Reviewed 2026-06-16: upgraded to KC 26.6.3 (netty 4.1.132 → 4.1.133). Resolved &
# removed CVE-2026-4282/4634/4636 (KC app), CVE-2026-42579/42583/42584/42587 (netty
# 4.1.133) and CVE-2026-34282 (openjdk). Remaining netty CVEs require 4.1.135.
# Verified by a Trivy 0.70.0 scan of the 26.6.3 image.
# Reviewed 2026-06-24: added CVE-2026-54512/54513 (jackson-databind 2.21.2 PolymorphicTypeValidator
# bypasses) newly appearing in Trivy Java DB. KC 26.6.3 bundles jackson-databind 2.21.2; fix requires
# 2.21.4, not yet shipped in a Keycloak release. Revisit the pinned digest when one lands.

